Titolo: Tunnels of Doom

Anno: 1982

Descrizione: Tunnels of Doom is a role-playing video game programmed by Kevin Kenney for the Texas Instruments TI-99/4A home computer and published by Texas Instruments on December 31, 1982. It was available in two formats: cartridge with accompanying disk and cartridge with cassette.Based loosely on the tabletop role-playing game Dungeons & Dragons, it is a dungeon crawl in which players control the fates of 1â€“4 characters as they navigate a maze of tunnels. Texas Instruments used the game in its marketing, citing it as entertainment software involving "strategy and logic".

